% heredoc strings
#"%%% SOME CUSTOM DELIMITER %%%"
This is a heredoc string with a custom delimiter.
It will be parsed as a string until the delimiter is reached.
It includes regular string functionality like {interpolation}, \{} \character escaping, etc.
The delimiter is not included in the string.
#%%% SOME CUSTOM DELIMITER %%%

% raw heredoc strings
#r"==== RAW HEREDOC DELIMITER ===="
This is a raw heredoc string with a custom delimiter.
It will be parsed as a string until the delimiter is reached.
It does not include {interpolation}, \{} \character escaping, etc.
==== RAW HEREDOC DELIMITER ====


